OL,3,CBan new, young drivers from carrying
OL,4,Cpassengers of similar age ` AA
OL,6,FNew drivers aged under 21 should be
OL,7,Fbanned from carrying passengers of a
OL,8,Fsimilar age for six months after
OL,9,Fpassing their test, a motoring
OL,10,Forganisation has claimed.
OL,12,FThe AA said it also wants those
OL,13,Fmotorists to be handed six penalty
OL,14,Fpoints for not wearing a seatbelt
OL,15,Fduring the same period, which would
OL,16,Fmean they lose their licence.
OL,18,FTo aid police enforcement a "G" plate
OL,19,Fshould be displayed on young drivers'
OL,20,Fcars, to highlight that they are a
OL,21,F"graduate" driver, the AA proposed.
